The paper discusses the impact of bit depth and measurement rate on compressive sensing, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also includes experiments on image reconstruction (cs.CV) and matrix completion (cs.MM), which further support these sub-categories.
